Before we proceed, I must ensure you understand your rights in this matter:

1. You have the right to remain silent. This means you do not have to speak or provide any information that could incriminate you.

2. You also have the right to have an attorney present during any questioning or legal proceedings. If you cannot afford an attorney, one will be appointed for you at no cost.

3. You have the right to a fair and public trial, where evidence will be presented, and witnesses can be called to testify on your behalf.

4. Furthermore, you have the right to confront witnesses against you, meaning you can question them in court.

5. Finally, you have the right to appeal any conviction or sentence imposed upon you.

PAPERLESS BRADY ORDER: It is ORDERED AND ADJUDGED that the Court confirms the State's obligation to disclose to the defendant all exculpatory evidencenamely, evidence that favors the defendant or casts doubt on the State's caseas required by the principles established in Brady v. Maryland, 373 U.S. 83 (1963) and its progeny. The State is hereby ORDERED to fulfill this obligation. The State has a duty to disclose any evidence that negates the defendant's guilt, affects the credibility of a witness, or could potentially reduce a sentence. The defendant is entitled to this information without needing to make a request. Failure to disclose exculpatory evidence in a timely manner may result in consequences, including, but not limited to, exclusion of evidence, dismissal of the information, contempt proceedings, disciplinary action, or sanctions by the Court. Signed by District Judge sadoimpacto (SJI) (Entered: 05/20/2025)

Opening Statement.

Thank you your Honour and may it please the court;

This case centers around one event arising on or about the 27th of April. Here, an innocent man, known as Stak1502, was walking around " The Hole " - a notoriously dangerous neighbourhood in Lander -, trying to spawn a vehicle. Unfortunately, this simple task was interrupted by the Defendant, whom, accompanied with a friend, shot and killed Stak1502 for no apparent reason.

Shooting this innocent man who was simply trying to spawn his car and likely exit the area, shooting this innocent man who hadn't interacted in any way with the Defendant or his affiliate, shooting this innocent man whilst the Defendant also had a Kilikov, an illegal firearm which can only bought by going through criminal networks, it shows the type of man that the Defendant is.

The Defendant is a merciless murderer - one who kills for no discernible reason -. For this reason, the State of Mayflower has brought forth this prosecution in the publics interest. Thank you your Honour.
